16 0 19 Butterfly Garden~
.At a young age, Randaran Alevain was struck with wanderlust and he left
the elven forest to see the world.  He spent many years traveling, and
eventually returned to the forest.  Upon his return, he met a fair elfess
named Alenda, and they were wed.  Alenda would listen for hours to
Randaran's tales of the wide world, and when he told her of his desire to
travel again, she was only too willing to accompany him.  They spent some
time traveling, and then the day came when they decided it was time to
settle down.  The Alevains bought a plot of land near Ceanshire, and
built themselves a small house.  Their first child was soon born, and
another followed not long after.

As time passed, the elder Alevains began to miss some of the elven fauna,
namely the gloriously coloured butterflies native to their homeland. 
Randaran decided that he would travel back to catch some, and bring them
back to share with his family and any other who would care to see them. 
A maze of hedge was built, to provide amusement for visitors as well as a
habitat for the insects.  So the Butterfly Gardens were conceived, and
the Alevain family has been caring for these delicate creatures ever
since.~

