0 0 0 Duergar~
.Average Statistics for Duergar

Height: male and female about 3'6" - 4'6"

Hair: Primarily shades of grey from medium to dark, rarely any lighter. 
Some older Duergar have been known to have their hair go white, but this
is rare and considered a throw back to their Dwarven origins.
All Duergar have thick grey beards matching the colour of their hair,
though it has become the trend among many Duergar to shave the top lip
lending their beard more of a face-framing quality.

Eyes: Shades of grey, occasionally so dark as to appear black.  Rarely
any lighter than medium grey.

Appearance: Duergar differ from their dwarven cousins in many key areas. 
Their skin is almost exclusively a mid grey in colour, generally a shade
or two lighter than their hair but rarely altering far to the darker or
lighter side from mid grey.  Duergar are quite a bit thinner than
dwarves, less broad across the shoulder and often less muscular.

Optional Advice on Role Playing a Duergar

Duergar are considered an evil race by many, and though one may find the
occasional individual with a more neutral calling in life you would never
find a Duergar supporting the cause of good.
Duergar society exists underground, and as such most duergar will have
spent the vast majority of their lives underground, giving rise to an
innate fear and distrust of all surface dwelling creatures.  Living
underground has also made the duergar most comfortable in darkness to the
extent that they will go out of their way to avoid exposing themselves to
excess light, particularly the daytime.
The influence this has had on the duergar as a race is marked, they are
most comfortable sneaking around and keeping to the shadows whenever
possible, lending to the rather natural feeling of distrust that they
provoke in most other races.

Racial Relations:

Duergar have inherited the ability (talent?) to hold a grudge to the
extreme from their cousins the dwarves.

Dwarves cannot be abided.  Duergar and dwarves hold a deepset and
unyielding hatred of everything the other embodies.  Other light races
are viewed with suspicion, although the duergar's withdrawn society means
that they have had little contact with these races and as such have not
had an opportunity to build up any substantial grudge.

Vyans are feared and mistrusted due to a past history ivolving
inslavement of the duergar by the vyans.

Goblins are the only race with which the duergar have friendly relations
