16 0 26 Geography~
.This continent is extremely active on a geological scale. The basic makeup
consists of three tectonic plates, with another three affecting them from
the ocean depths.  The map is purposefully sterile, so that we can alter
the world to our needs.

The southwestern section of the continent is termed 'The Plains of Anam'. 
The area is extremely fertile due to the three main rivers of the
continent providing water for the area.  This is basically the 'bread
basket' of the continent a la US Midwest.

The eastern section of the continent is rolling plains, including beyond
the cold line, where they turn into sub-arctic rolling plains gradually. 
Eventually this will be Tundra-type terrain 

The islands to the south are technically glaciers, covered in ice and
inhospitable to most creatures, they will be useable for zones after we
add in boat travel.  These islands were created via an impact site of a
very large meteor.  The single island in the center with a mountain would
be either extremely magical or a magical dead zone probably based on the
properties of the meteor.

Most shipping will occur from the western bay toward the north, very
little travel would occur through the southern waters, any city there
would send goods via land, over a mountain trail and across the wide
plains, rather than brave the ice-ridden southern ocean.  The small plot
of land on the extreme northwestern corner of the map, (could be an
island, could be yet another small continent) should have a pirate town
on it, it would be the logical place for them to be.  Their placement
there would allow them to intercept ships traveling between the good
towns on the oceans.

The salt lake in the middle of the twin mountain ranges is a legitimate
geological occurrence, highly saturated and with absolutely no river,
either above ground or below feeding into or out of it.  This occurred
because the northwestern plate is pulling away from the southeastern and
western plates, at the same time the southeastern and western plates are
colliding, causing the mountain ranges.

The twin mountain ranges are extremely geologically active earthquakes
and volcanoes are abundant.  Mar Quoith situated around the small valley
that has a bay access in the southern half of the eastern most mountain
range.  The city being there would also allow raids on the farmers in the
western plain.  The twin mountain ranges are extremely large, about the
size of the Himalayas, which of course has peaks tens of thousands of
feet high.

Dun Tathaig (main light city, although light is hardly the proper term
for such a place) should be on the western bay, with a second city at the
base of the mountains by the river that leads to it.  This river would
allow very quick travel time between the two cities.  There would almost
definitely be a third city at the mouth of the second river to the south
of that, allowing even more shipping of goods between the three towns. 
The large eastern lake would no doubt have a canal built on it leading
out to the northern bay where there would be yet another city.

The mountain range on the western continent would probably house the
dwarves as these will be the oldest mountains.  Very little geological
activity occurs with them, though there is a small plate that still
affects them, they are in no way as active as the twin mountain ranges.

These are the notes Adakar sent me to accompany the map I should be
receiving early next week.  All names (I added them) are subject to
change.~

