16 0 19 Mar Quioth~
.The crown jewel of the underground realms, Mar Quioth is the central
haven of the dark races.  The city's name translates roughly from the
Vyan tongue to 'The Realm of Shadows.' When the racial split occured on
A'lainn, the dark races wandered for many months before choosing this
place to make their homeland.  Nestled deep in the K'tathi Mountains, Mar
Quioth is nothing if not beautiful.

As the years rolled past, the Realm of Shadows grew into a sprawling
system commonly broken into six separate cities for the sake of ease. 
@cSha'rheza@n, or the Old City, is the original core of Mar Quioth, and
is the home of the wealthy and influential members of dark society.  Only
the finest merchandise is sold on these austere streets; costly prices
ensure that only the wealthy need shop here.  Sha'rheza also holds the
residence of the leader of Mar Quioth.

@cSha'darci@n, or the New City (the term new is relevant; while nowhere
near as old as Sha'rheza, the so-called 'new' city has been in existence
for several hundred years), is the merchant's quarter.  From finery to
every-day goods, something to suit every taste can be found in this
place, though the elite tend to prefer the more trendy boutiques of
Sha'rheza.  This is also where the majority of the residents of Mar
Quioth make their homes; in general, this sector is elegant, yet nowhere
near a match to Sha'rheza's grand beauty.

As rules outlining the use of magics became more and more strict, many
schools of wizardry were outlawed, and it was decreed that magics could
only be taught in crown-approved universities.  @cSha'myrsa@n, the City
of Lights, holds the oldest and finest of the schools of dark magic, and
is also home to several temples and libraries.  Many people fear the
magics constantly going on in the City of Lights, and as a result, this
quarter tends to remain rather desolate of all but the mages, their
students, and those few seeking the knowledge of the libraries or the
peace of the temples.

Every city has its poorer section, and Mar Quioth, grand though it is, is
no exception.  Commonly referred to as the Warren, @cSha'maral'dze@n, the
City of Rats, is the most notorious section of town.  This is the realm
of beggars and criminals, low lifes who haven't worked a day of their
miserable lives and don't intend to start anytime soon.  Those items
deemed too outrageous even by the relatively free and easy standards of
Mar Quioth can usually be found here, and indeed it's rumoured that
virtually anything can be bought in the Warren...for a dear price. 
Several attempts have been made to clean out this unsavory sector of the
city, but like the rats they're named after, the dealers here just have a
habit of popping back up in this maze of dark allies and shabby buildings.

Partly to deal with the pests in Sha'maral'dze, a small, carefully
selected army is maintained at all times.  These elite fighting troops
make their homes in @cSha'ke'chani@n, the City of Blood.  The best
training grounds and veteran warriors can be found here, and many young
recruits flock to this place hoping to become members of the
Ke'chan'edras, the Queen's personal guards.  This part of Mar Quioth is
rather spartan, the warriors caring more for their training and duty than
for the luxuries much of the city has to offer.

The last of the six cities of Mar Quioth is @cSha'kymor'al@n, the City of
Ships.  This is the youngest part of the Realm of Shadows, and unlike the
rest, is found on the surface world.  A healthy, if somewhat tense, trade
has been founded between Dun Tathaig and Mar Quioth, as well as the other
cities of the land.  As a result, this shantytown of social outcasts and
rabble-rousers of every sort has sprung up around the docks of
Sha'kymor'al, providing a haven for thieves and others of less than noble
professions.  Many of the nobles of Mar Quioth would prefer to pretend
that this surface city wasn't part of the Realm of Shadows at all, but
the trade is quite profitable, so this 'eyesore' is tolerated, if not
widely accepted.~

