.+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                             |
|                  Immortal Help File:  Mob Checklist                         |
|                                                                             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

This help file is designed as a checklist for people to quickly review their
mobs to make sure that important fields have been entered before submitting
for review.

MSETS

Nation     : If a mob should affect reputations, a field should be set here.
Level      : What level of experience is the mob standardized for?
Sex        : Male/Female/Neutral/Random
Coins      : How many coins should this mob hold every reset?
Size       : How big is the mob?  Important for sized rooms and custom.fit armor.
Hitdice    : How many hit points does the mob have?  (Standards!)
Group      : Is the mob a member of a group for helpcalling/assisting?
Race       : What kind of race is this mob?
Wander     : How fast/slow should this mob move around? (if not sentinel)
Weight     : Weight is important for corpses
Price      : If this mob can be sold at a pet shop it needs a price set
Alignment  : Makes a difference for tallying kills/reputations
Light      : Does this mob carry his/her own light source? (emulated)
Skeleton   : Can this mob be turned into a skeletal pet for clerics?
Zombie     : Can this mob be turned into a zombie pet for clerics?
Corpse     : Does this mob generate a different corpse than normal?
Str        : Strength plays an important part in combat
Dex        : How well does your mob dodge hits?  Important in combat
Mag        : How well does your mob resist magical hits like magic missile?
Fir        : How well does your mob resist fire attacks?
Col        : How well does your mob resist cold attacks?
Min        : How well does your mob resist mind attacks like sleep?
Ele        : How well does your mob resist electrical attacks?
Aci        : How well does your mob resist acid attacks?
Poi        : How well does your mob resist being poisoned?
Name       : If your mob is a shopkeeper or a unique humanoid mob, it should
             have a name.  What is their name?
Singular   : Equivalent to a player's appearance, but shorter.  Important!
Long_S     : Action field.  Are they standing, sitting, looking at you?
Plural     : You never know when two might be standing there.  When you create
             a new mob the code does not format plurals properly very often.
Long_P     : Action field for groups.  What are they doing?
Keywords   : Important field if you want to goto this mob later.
Color      : Should this mob stand out from the background?

MFLAGS

Sentinel     : If you want a mob to stand still all the time, set this flag.
Can.Tame     : If this flag is set, someone can tame it.  Very important.
Aggressive   : Leaps to attack any player it sees.
Stay.Area    : Wandering mobs stay within their own area with this flag on.
Wimpy        : Mobs can flee during combat if this flag is on.
Humanoid     : Mobs can be swept-kicked/tripped if this flag is on.
             : Also determines that they can sweep kick others.
Summonable   : Mobs will run to their chief/etc. if helpcalled (see group!)
Assist.Group : Mobs will autoassist their own group members in the same room.
Can.Swim     : Important field if water is in a zone or it can be a pet.
Has.Eyes     : Mob can be eye gouged or blinded if this flag is on.
Ghost        : If set, doesn't have a corpse, floats, has no eyes
No.Bash      : Important for big mobs, guards, shopkeepers, etc.
Use.The      : If a character should show up as 'the chief' instead of
               'a chief', use this flag.
Approved     : If this flag is set, you cannot change any mob settings.
               Contact Tyrone or Eliza to get this removed.
Sanctuary    : Mob cannot be killed - Shopkeepers, trainers, etc.
Sleep.Resist : Mob cannot be put to sleep.
Poison.Resis : Mob cannot be poisoned.


MARMOR

Marmor must be set, no matter what kind of mob it is!  At least 3 examples!

MPCODE
Each mob needs a standard set of attack code.  See the help files for standard
levels of damage a mob should dish out.

MPROGS

If a mob has special code (ie: It junks its sword upon death, it talks to any
player who walks in the room, etc) make sure all fields are filled in and the
code is properly working.

MRESETS

Re-rolls      : Make sure objects are properly lined up and their re-rolls are
                set for proper object loading
1_ch          : Make sure the percentages are low/high enough.  Every mob
               should wear a basic set of clothing, and rare objects should
                be rare - 1 to 5% at most.
Rust          : Most metal objects should load at 99% rusty unless justified.
Position      : Make sure worn objects are positioned in a body slot

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+~

