.New Mob Standards -- 10-22-99
                     01-15-00 @YUpdated@n
                     01-25-00 @RFinalized@n
                     07-04-00 @MUpdated for Wielding@n
                     10-18-02 @GUpdated for Marmor@n
@I@I@I@I@I@I@I@I@I@I 11-24-03 @GUpdated for Pets Again@n

@R1)@n Hitdice for mobs.
@C*@n Levels  1-40 - leveld10+(10*Level).
           Ave - 15.5*level.
@C*@n Levels 40-80 - leveld12+(12*Level).
           Ave - 18.5*level.
@C*@n Levels 80-90 - leveld15+(15*Level).
           Ave - 23.0*level.

Note: d10 = 5.5 average. d15 = 8 average, etc.

----------------------------------------------------------
- i.e. for a level  2 mob....................2d10+20.
- i.e. for a level 40 mob....................40d12+480.
- i.e. for a level 80 mob....................80d15+1200.
                         @M*****@n
Of course 80d15 is an awfully random hitpoint mob so 20d10+2200 would be
a better choice and much more predictable.

----------------------------------------------------------
@R2)@n Mpcode Damage for mobs.
              Tank Damage              Randoms
@C*@n Levels 1-40 - 4*Level                 2*Level
@C*@n Levels 40-80- 5*Level                 3*Level
@C*@n Levels 80-90- 6*Level                 3*Level
                         @M*****@n
- Tank damage includes any attack that cannot target a random character
in the room and does not include area attacks.
- Random attacks are calculated by taking the max damage of the attack
times the % chance of its occurance ( Count area attacks only once ).
- Area attacks use the following equation (in order to give the players a
chance) 
       @Y ( 4 * % chance of occurance * damage )@n
@Y***@n  Healing costs are factored into mpcode damage ratings!
- use the following simple formula..
       @Y( hps healed * percentage chance of occurance ) * @e.@n@Y75@n
----------------------------------------------------------
@R3)@n Marmor for mobs.
@C*@n Level 1-20 max marmor is 1-2 per any one location.
@C*@n Level 20-60 max marmor is 1/4 Mob level.
@C*@n Level 60-90 max marmor is equal to 1/3 Mob level.
There are always exceptions to this within reason.
                         @M*****@n
- i.e. for a level 1  mob...................... marmor 1000 1 toughened skin
- i.e. for a level 20 mob...................... marmor 1000 7 grizzled arm
- i.e. for a level 60 mob...................... marmor 1000 20 heavily scaled body
-------------------------------------------------------------
@R4) Coins.@n
@YCoin standards will be in-place when the final economy is finalized.@n
-------------------------------------------------------------
@R5) Wielding and Non-wielding.@n
Mobs that reset and wield weapons, must have separate mpcode for wielding
and non-wielding damage.  Use of the is_wearing() functions checks to see
what item the mob is 'wielding'.  Damage from wielding mobs should be
(except in the 5 and lower level category) 10-25% more, the higher the
level of the mob, the more damage it should be performing.  This also
applies to area attacks that involve the weapon (not a normal case).
-------------------------------------------------------------
@R6) Guard/Protector Mob Levels.@n
-------------------------------------------------------------
Below is a list of the different types of protector mobs and their
@Capproximate@n levels.

Level 50-60 for city guards.
Level 40-45 for warders and rangers.
Level 50-65 for army soldiers.
Level 65-75 for officers.
Level 80+ for special commanders.
------------------------------------------------------------------ 
@R7) Pets.@n
Pets use two sets of mpcode, a set of mpcode that is used when it is not
a pet, and a set of when it is a pet.  The mpcode for pets when it is a
pet is 80% of the mob standard for its mob damage.
Pets should not have 100% mind resistance.
Experienced pet damage function assumes an average of 3 attacks per
round, try not to stray too far from this.
~

