16 0 27 mobguide1~
.+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                             |
|                  Immortal Help File:  Mob Checklist Part 1/5                |
|                                                                             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

This help file is designed to give a quick crash course for newer immortals
into mob creation, and give a checklist of sorts each builder knows what fields
should be set and how they can be entered.  If in doubt, take a peek at other
mobs that are similar to what you want that already exist, or ask for help.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=> MSETS <=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

In most of these fields, if you are unsure what values are applicable, type
mset and the field name by itself.  A list of possible values will appear.

Nation       : This field is used for mobs whose death will cause shifts
               in a player's reputation.  Primarily used for mobs that reside
               in a town.  Set this field to the 'clan' they belong to.
Level        : What level of experience is the mob?
               Make sure the level of the mob fits your zone profile
Fame         : Not used at this time
Sex          : male, female, neutral, or random
Coins        : The amount of coins that your mob should be holding on a
               regular basis.  Don't mreset coins, use this field.
Size         : How big is your mob?  Note:  Changing races does not
               automatically update this field.
Hitdice      : How many hit points does your mob have?  See the help file
               mob_standards for standards information.
Maturity     : Not used at this time
Group        : Mobs who are designed to assist each other in battle, or be
               able to be summoned by their chief if he/she's attacked need
               to have this field set to a common value.  You can use a pre-set
               group name, or have one created for you.  Values stored in a
               table called groups.
Kills        : Game tallies how many times the mob has been killed
Race         : What race is your mob supposed to be?  Type mset race to see a
               list of available races.  Note:  Nation and size are not updated
               when you set race, you must adjust those manually.
Wander       : If a mob is able to walk around (see mflag sentinel), this field
(200-4999)     determines how fast they will change rooms.  Default is 4000,
               the lower the number the faster they move.
Weight       : How much does your mob weigh?  This field is important for
               corpses, because almost every mob uses a generic corpse which
               use this field's setting to determine how much it should weigh.
Mvdice       : How many movement points should your mob have?  Mobs which stay
               within their own zone can have the default left alone, but mobs
               which might be used as pets should have this value adjusted
               higher.
Price        : This field is used for animals which can be bought in a pet shop.
               This field sets the price for the animal.
Deaths       : Code automatically tracks how many times this mob has died.
Alignment    : Is your mob good or neutral or evil?
Light        : Does your mob carry its own light?  Traditionally mobs do not,
               because the room will usually be lit if it needs to be.  A
               normal ball of light has a setting of 50.
Adult        : This will be used when maturity is fully in effect.
Skeleton     : If a cleric can use their spell greater animation on this mob's
               corpse to turn it into a skeletal pet, mset the skeleton that is
               created in this field.  (ie: a skeletal ferret for a ferret).
               The skeletal pet must already exist and have a mob number.
Zombie       : Same as skeleton, but for the spell animate dead.
