mobs that are similar to what you want that already exist, or ask for help.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=> MPCODE <=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

The method in which mobs attack players is determined using mpcode (mob code).
This code is looped once per round, so make sure you aren't choreographing an
entire battle on one page.  The best way to make a good combat routine is to
find a mob whose fighting style mimics the way you want your new mob to fight,
and copy/paste the majority of the combat code, making modifications for damage
and hit names.

The amount of damage a mob should deal to a player/group is displayed in the
help file mob_standards.

MPCODE can also refer to specialty mob programs.  Use the command MPEDIT to
create these special code styles, which are coded very similarly to acodes or
mpcodes, but ch defaults to the mob itself, and victim = the person the mob
is directing the action against.

Since disarm is now a viable option, make sure you code any mob who wields a
weapon properly.  See bugbears/hobgoblins/kobolds for proper methods of
handling this issue.  If you need any assistance with mob attack programs,
contact Tyrone, Adakar, or Rikahn.

