16 0 16 Room.check.list~
.This is a @Creference only@n help file for builders.  Remember, our goal
is to create as realistic, interactive world as possible through text.

When creating rooms, be sure the following fields are set appropriately:

@CSize@n - Consider the setting of the zone.  Would you want elephants
running through a farmhouse?
@CTerrain@n - Terrain determines how much movement is used.  Make sure it
is appropriate to the setting.
@CFilename@n - so we can find your area file easily
@CRoom Name@n - See Help Room_names
@CLevel@n - Approximate level of a group that can safely run the zone.
@CHelp file@n - All areas MUST have a help file.  See @Ghelp area help
files@n for setting one up.

@CRflags@n that should be looked at on every room are:

Lit - Whether a room would be logically lit.  If not, do not set this
flag.
Underground
Indoors
Any flag for special rooms, such as banks, shops or altars
No.mount - Decide if you want players to bring horses and/or pets into
the rooms.
No.mob - Do you want wandering mobs to roam here.
Extras
Randoms
Leaving codes
Interactive acodes such as searches.

@CRoom descriptions@n:

Room descriptions should be a decent length (I'd like to see at least
five lines or more for each, although I @emight@n consider shorter if the
content is very good).  No three-liners will be approved.  Also, the
content of the room descriptions should allow for further exploration,
