16 0 2 spoison~
.@CSYNTAX@n

spoison( char, stat, save, modifier, affect );

@CPARAMETERS@n

char - The character to poison.
stat - The stat to reduce. @Y(See help stat type)@n
modifier - the maximum modifier to apply.
save - whether the target gets a save or not. (1 = yes, anything else = no );
affect - a character affect to attach to the poison, will only function
with normal poison ( stat = none ) 

@CDESCRIPTION@n

This will afflict char with a custom poison.  When used in conjunction
with thief poison skill, the duration, level, and strength of the poison
are dependant on their skill.  In this case modifier can be used to make
this particular poison more or less deadly.  When used in any other code
modifier will determine the poisons strength.
Save should be set to no on thief poison (the routine already has a save
built in), and usually yes on any other call.

@CEXAMPLE@n

spoison( ch, str, -5, 1 );
Will afflict char with a poison draining -1 to -5 strength.
OR
With poison skill, this will make the thiefs poison -1 to -5 points stronger.

spoison( ch, dex, 10, 1 );
Will have no effect
OR
With poison skill, this will make the thiefs poison 1 to 10 points weaker.

~

