Creator: Teircen

The elven woods.  Actually, per request, this is to be a rather large
zone.  I can forsee having to break it up into more than one zone to make
it make more sense.  Within the woods there are two elven settlements. 
The larger high-elven city, a bastion of elven magic, politics and
culture and the smaller wood-elf village, a quiet abode in tune with
nature and concealed from prying eyes.  The high elven village will
contain a library, alchemists, a temple and city-style shops.  It will
not contain spells commonly attributed to elemental or nature magics,
that has fallen to the wood-elves.  A fair comparison would be city-folk
and country-folk but in elven terms.  Being somewhat xenophonic, the
elves have not cut trails into or out of the woods and only the natural
animal trails facilitate travel.
However, these are not the woodlands of the elven homelands and this
forest dose have its darker side.  Rabies is not unknown in the animals
of the woods.  Animals both sick and twisted to the darker forces dwell
here in conflict with the more peaceful animals the elves are accustomed
to living with.  Poachers frequent the woods in search of game.  A fallen
ruin deep within the woods contains twisted powers of necromancy and the
occasional ghoul finds its way into the lush foliage to plague the local
elves.

== Elves born of this region, having lived and grown here and being elves
by their nature, will have an easier time traversing the woods.  If there
