16 0 5 TFH.Armor.Decrepit~
.@YDECREPIT ARMOR@n
@CARMOR STYLE: MELTABLE@n

Decrepit armor is designed solely for the use of popping on mobs to
provide meltable metal armor to players without resetting the kind of
stuff that players would normally want to wear (aka: Avoid the gluttony
of ringmail/scalemail/chainmail that trolls, dwarves, barbarians, etc. 
provided...  Virtually nobody customed metal armor unless it was
platemail/plate armor...  this is going to change.) 

@YIMPORTANT INFORMATION@n

Decrepit armor should almost always be rusted, the more the better.  Set
rust to at least 99-100% on mobs that reset this.  The armor is wearable,
but the AC and durability is but a shadow of the customed versions.

This armor is designed to be what players melt in order to custom the
metal classes of armor, from banded to plate armor.  Reset this armor
wisely.  In lower level areas, it should only reset on
chief/bodyguard/sentry type of mobs, and not 100%.

Higher level areas may use this as a more common alternative to leather
objects, but do not have an area load metal armor 100% on all mobs... 
Metal is supposed to be VERY RARE these days, players should not be able
to make custom metal armor without considerable effort on their part.

