16 0 19 Tirath Regnus~
.,------^------,
< Tirath Regnus >
`------v------`
Duroth claimed the mighty spirit of the striped-socks king (Soiran I)
just after Dartanian shook the mountains, driving the goblin hoards back
to the depths of the Gilmil's Heel (Calyn Rift).  A great celebration
ensued among the dwarves of Lonilan - the horde invasion averted, the
striped-socks king taking his place beside Duroth - there was much
merriment and joy such as dwarvenkind had never seen.  Firebreather
flowed free through the streets of Lonilan and the twelve drums,
accompanied by the beardless prince's (Soiran II) breath-pipe players,
belted out the sounds of victory.  History remembered this day as the
Feast of Dartanian - traditionally dwarves wear striped-socks on this
feast day. It remains, to this day, as the only high feast the beardless
breath-pipe players play.

The beardless prince charged Drolm Dromli of the dwarven labor union with
the task of constructing his father's final resting place.  A spot was
chosen within Tirath Regnus - home of the High Priest of Duroth and
ceremonial burial place for the warriors of Lonilan.  Miners tripled
their ruby and diamond output - the colors red and white being the royal
colors of the line of Soiran.  Carved within the hard brown mountain
stone of the tomb were larger-than-life sized images of the striped-socks
king, complete with diamond encrusted armor set right into the stone.
Golden thrones, chariots, goblets, vases, candelabras - almost anything
gold could be molded into - were all placed within the tomb.  When all
work was complete, all the warriors of Lonilan clad in full ceremonial
garb gathered within the tomb to witness the final sealing.

The high priest of Duroth buried Striped-socks, clad in his newly-polished
battle gear - consisting of a black steel breastplate inset with diamonds
and rubies, a black circular steel shield with Soiran's royal crest
engraved upon it, a black steel cap with horns taken from the alpha male of
a mountain ram colony, and (the centerpiece of the collection) his sturdy
axe -- the very piece of equipment which separated him from other warriors.
Many dwarves spent uncounted sums money to get the master smiths of Lonilan
to forge them an axe of great power.  Striped-socks however, forged his own
blade at the age of ninety-one.  It fell short of all the standards lain
down so long ago by the Blacksmith's Guild.  It was unbalanced - had a
wooden hilt rather than the preferred iron or steel - and no carvings or
frills master smiths are so apt at decorating with.  Yet striped-socks took
great pride in it.  To this day it has dealt more deathblows than any
other... all dealt by the arm of striped-socks.~

.****MAJOR LANDMARKS****
The River Tellach
Cugal Falls on the River Tellach
king, complete with diamond encrusted armor set right into the stone.~

0 0 19 Tireth's Swamp~
.A great evil has begun to make its presence known in the area just north of
Sos-Kul.  The harbinger of this news is the wife of a young sage.  Relanya
has been seen around Medienne spreading news of the death of her husband,
Tireth.  Rumors of a dark infernalist summoning armies of demons to act as
the forward attack on all of the races of the world have begun to circulate
through the cliques of those that practice the dark arts.  Combined with
these rumors are the reports of a young lizardman hunter, the fierce and
dreaded k'sskians, which have been thought extinct for generations, have
returned to the world.~

.~

