16 0 4 Weapon Standards~
.@CDamage Calculation for Weapons@n

@C--Weapon Type---------Damage Formula-------------Damdice@n

@CDaggers@n@I@I@I@I@I@Glevel of weapon / 2 + 6@n@I@I@I@I@I@R2d@n
@CUnarmed@n@I@I@I@I@I@Glevel of weapon / 3 + 6@n@I@I@I@I@I@R1d@n
@CWhips/Clubs@n      @Glevel of weapon / 2 + 8@n@I@I@I@I@I@R1d@n
@CSwords@n@I@I@I@I@I @Glevel of weapon * 2/3 + 6 + wgt@n@I@R2d@n
@C2hd-Swords@n@I@I@I @Glevel of weapon * 2/3 + 6 + 2*wgt@n@R2d@n
@CStaves/Spears@n@I@I@Glevel of weapon * 2/3 + 10@n@I@I@I @R3d@n
@CMaces/Axes@n@I@I@I @Glevel of weapon * 3/4 + 12@n@I@I@I @R4d@n
@CPolearm@n@I@I@I@I@I@Glevel of weapon + 16@n@I@I@I@I@I@I @R5d@n

@CCrossbows@n        @Glevel of weapon * 3/4 + 10@n @I@I@I@R2d@n
@CBows@n             @Glevel of weapon * 2/3 + 6@n@I@I@I@I@R1d@n
@CSlings@n           @Glevel of weapon / 2 + 6@n@I@I@I@I@I@R1d@n

@CAmmunition@n      @Glevel of ammunition / 4 + 4@n @I@I@I@R1d@n

Level 1 weapons are treated as level 0 for standards purposes.

@CDice Progression@n

Every 30 levels the damdice get moved up 1.

For example a level 1 dagger, with no specials.
0/2+6=6 max damage for it.
Then take max damage and divide it by the number of damdice it gets.
So 6/2=3.  So damage is 2d3 for a level 1 dagger.

@COpcode Specials@n

These are treated on an individual basis, but in general you take the
frequency * max damage of the special, and reduce max damage of the
weapon by that amount.

So for example, a random of 1 to 10 == 4 is 10%
If the special maxes at 70 points, you get 70*.1 = 7 points off max
damage.

Wear opcodes will usually count for nothing.  They are just pretty.

To see the affects of status changes on an item, look at help status affects.
~

