0 0 20 Wimpy~
.@CSYNTAX@n

wimpy                   : list current wimpy settings.
wimpy <field> <% value> : sets your wimpy to a % value of your max hps.
wimpy <field>           : resets the %value of that field to zero.

@CDESCRIPTION@n

Wimpy causes you to flee when your hit points go below your wimpy % value.
You will attempt to flee automatically, so remember to turn it off at the
appropriate times or it could get you into more trouble than whatever good
it may do.  Your maximum wimpy % value depends upon level and your maximum
hit points.  Note that wimpy is @CNOT@n failsafe, and comes with no ironclad
guarantees, but it's usually better than nothing.

The available fields are @CFlee@n, @CBlink@n, @CRecall@n and @CPray@n.  When your hit
points go below the % value of a field, you will attempt to either flee,
recite a scroll of recall if you have one, or cast the spell 'blink' if you
are a mage.  Again, this is not failsafe, so be warned.
~

